  "prompt": "Which are the best poems about India?",
  "response": "India, with its rich cultural heritage and diverse traditions, has inspired many poets to pen down their thoughts and feelings about the country. Here are some notable poems about India that have been widely appreciated:\n\n1. **\"Where the Mind is Without Fear\" by Rabindranath Tagore**\n   - This is an excerpt from Tagore's famous work \"Gitanjali.\" It expresses a vision of an ideal India, free from fear and narrow-mindedness, where knowledge is free and the head is held high.\n\n2. **\"To India \u2013 My Native Land\" by Henry Louis Vivian Derozio**\n   - Written in the early 19th century, this poem reflects the poet's deep love for his country and a lament for its lost glory. It is a passionate call for the revival of India's past grandeur.\n\n3. **\"Discovery of India\" by Sarojini Naidu**\n   - Known as the \"Nightingale of India,\" Naidu's poetry often celebrated the beauty and diversity of the Indian subcontinent. This poem reflects her deep connection to the land and its people.\n\n4. **\"Mother India\" by Subramania Bharati**\n   - This poem by the Tamil poet Bharati is a powerful expression of patriotism and devotion to the motherland. It invokes the spirit of unity and resilience among Indians.\n\n5. **\"A Tryst with Destiny\" by Jawaharlal Nehru**\n   - Although not a traditional poem, Nehru's historic speech at the stroke of midnight on August 15, 1947, is often recited and celebrated as a poetic expression of India's newfound freedom and the challenges ahead.\n\n6. **\"Ode to India\" by Nissim Ezekiel**\n   - Ezekiel, one of India's foremost poets in English, often wrote about his experiences and reflections on Indian society. This poem captures the complexities and contradictions of modern India.\n\nThese poems offer a glimpse into the multifaceted beauty and the deep emotional connection poets have with India. Each poem, in its unique way, celebrates the country's spirit, struggles, and aspirations.",
